From 2a67be9a83101d5c2590a58f22ce4c37a3f9c2aa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 07:42:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add NAS/DLNA library browsing and album playback

Browse a UPnP/DLNA media server (Synology, MiniDLNA, Asset UPnP,
Plex/Jellyfin) as an album-art grid and play a whole album on a WiiM
device. The WiiM HTTP API can't browse content, so the dashboard talks to
the media server directly over UPnP SOAP and drives playback with the
LinkPlay setPlayerCmd:playlist command (the device fetches a generated
m3u, then streams each track straight from the NAS).

- New src/lib/dlna/ client: SSRF-pinned plain-HTTP transport that reuses
  the WiiM resolveTarget/pinnedLookup guard (now exported); device
  description -> ContentDirectory resolution; Search with a shallow-Browse
  fallback; a tolerant DIDL-Lite parser; an Extended-M3U builder; and
  short-TTL HMAC tokens for the playlist callback.
- Routes: GET /api/nas/browse, GET /api/nas/art (pinned image proxy),
  POST /api/devices/[id]/nas/play, and a deliberately unauthenticated,
  token-guarded GET /api/nas/m3u that the device fetches over the LAN.
- Settings: media-server description URL + a Library card toggle; new
  MEDIA_CALLBACK_ORIGIN env var for reverse-proxy setups.
- UI: a Library entry card and an album-grid browse dialog.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
